cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.CE, cs.SOC

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper uses data from a location-based social service, Foursquare, to analyze the impact of the Olympic Games on local retailers. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the economic impact of a large-scale event on a city and how location-based social networks can be used to assess this impact. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper uses supervised learning techniques to predict the success of businesses based on geographic and mobility factors. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is another possible category as the paper applies computational methods to analyze the impact of the Olympic Games on local retailers. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the social and economic implications of the Olympic Games on local businesses.
